-- UniCredit to Name Only One General Manager in New Structure, MF Reports
-- B y   J e r r o l d   C o l t e n
-- 2010-10-08T05:49:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-08/unicredit-to-name-only-one-general-manager-in-new-structure-mf-reports.html
UniCredit SpA has decided to name
only one general manager in its new management structure, MF
reported, without saying where it got the information.  Chief Executive Officer Federico Ghizzoni and Chairman
Dieter Rampl will go to Washington today to brief Bank of Italy
Governor Mario Draghi on the plan, MF said. Sergio Ermotti and
Paolo Fiorentino are the top candidates for the job, according
to MF.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jerrold Colten at 
 jcolten@bloomberg.net  